{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SectionModelRef"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkSectionModel"},{"type":"text","text":" groups successive items into so-called sections. List widgets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListView"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkGridView"},{"type":"text","text":" then allow displaying section headers for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these sections by installing a header factory."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Many GTK list models support sections inherently, or they pass through the sections"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a model they are wrapping."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the section groupings of a model change, the model will emit the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SectionModel::sections-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] signal by calling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.SectionModel.sections_changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] function. All sections in the given range"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then need to be queried again."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The [signal"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ListModel::items-changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] signal has the same effect, all sections in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that range are invalidated, too."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":